  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "Choosing the right karaoke song can make all the difference, especially when considering your vocal range. As a 2nd alto, you likely have a rich lower register with comfortable singing ranges typically spanning from F\u2083 to F\u2085. Here are some karaoke-friendly songs that suit a 2nd alto voice, spanning various genres to match different moods and preferences:\n\n### **Pop Hits**\n1. **Adele \u2013 \"Someone Like You\"**\n   - A soulful ballad that showcases emotional depth and lower vocal ranges.\n2. **Alicia Keys \u2013 \"If I Ain't Got You\"**\n   - Perfect for highlighting a smooth, rich vocal tone.\n3. **Ariana Grande \u2013 \"Almost Is Never Enough\" (duet with Nathan Sykes)**\n   - Combines lower and higher ranges, allowing for expressive singing.\n4. **Adele \u2013 \"Rolling in the Deep\"**\n   - Energetic and powerful, great for showcasing vocal strength.\n\n### **Rock Classics**\n1. **Aerosmith \u2013 \"I Don\u2019t Want to Miss a Thing\"**\n   - A powerful rock ballad that suits lower to mid-range voices.\n2. **Toni Braxton \u2013 \"Un-Break My Heart\"**\n   - Although more R&B, it's a dramatic choice that fits well within an alto range.\n3. **Fleetwood Mac \u2013 \"Landslide\"**\n   - A softer rock choice with a comfortable range for altos.\n\n### **R&B & Soul**\n1. **Etta James \u2013 \"At Last\"**\n   - A timeless classic that highlights lower vocal registers beautifully.\n2. **Lauryn Hill \u2013 \"Ex-Factor\"**\n   - Combines soulful melodies with manageable vocal ranges.\n3. **Bill Withers \u2013 \"Ain\u2019t No Sunshine\"**\n   - Simple yet impactful, ideal for expressive altos.\n\n### **Country Favorites**\n1. **Dolly Parton \u2013 \"Jolene\"**\n   - A country classic with a melody that suits lower female voices.\n2. **Miranda Lambert \u2013 \"The House That Built Me\"**\n   - Emotional storytelling that aligns well with an alto\u2019s expressive capabilities.\n3. **Kacey Musgraves \u2013 \"Slow Burn\"**\n   - A modern country tune with a relaxed tempo and comfortable range.\n\n### **Musical Theatre**\n1. **\"Flower Duet\" from *Lakm\u00e9***\n   - A beautiful duet that emphasizes lower harmonies.\n2. **\"You\u2019ll Never Walk Alone\" from *Carousel***\n   - A powerful anthem that showcases vocal depth.\n3. **\"Defying Gravity\" from *Wicked*** (choose the alto-friendly sections)\n   - Offers dramatic flair with parts suitable for lower ranges.\n\n### **Other Suggestions**\n1. **Billie Holiday \u2013 \"All of Me\"**\n   - A jazz standard that utilizes rich, lower tones.\n2. **Sade \u2013 \"Smooth Operator\"**\n   - A sultry, smooth track perfect for an alto\u2019s velvety voice.\n3. **Johnny Cash \u2013 \"Ring of Fire\"** (if comfortable with gender role flexibility)\n   - Embracing a deeper range and adding a unique twist to karaoke sessions.\n\n### **Tips for Selecting Karaoke Songs as a 2nd Alto:**\n- **Know Your Range:** Always be aware of your comfortable singing range to avoid straining your voice.\n- **Choose Familiar Songs:** Picking songs you know well can boost confidence and performance.\n- **Consider the Key:** Some karaoke platforms allow you to adjust the key of the song. If a song is slightly out of your range, lowering the key can make it more manageable.\n- **Express Emotion:** Select songs that resonate with you emotionally, as this can enhance your performance regardless of technical range.\n\nRemember, the best karaoke performance comes from enjoying the song and expressing yourself, so choose tracks that make you feel confident and excited to sing. Have fun!",
